        "title": "fix(codex): restore openai-codex catalog alias",
        "body": "Closes #94184.\n\nRestores the legacy `openai-codex` provider ref as a Codex catalog alias so upgraded app-server configs keep resolving the Codex model catalog. The Codex provider discovery entry now exposes the same hook alias, with regression coverage for model listing and `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` resolution through the bundled provider static catalog.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: `openai-codex` provider refs should resolve the Codex provider catalog after enabling the Codex plugin.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch, OpenClaw 2026.6.8 (`ba6abd3`), with a temporary config containing `{\"plugins\":{\"entries\":{\"codex\":{\"enabled\":true}}}}`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Created a temporary config, forced offline Codex catalog fallback with `OPENCLAW_CODEX_DISCOVERY_LIVE=0`, and ran `pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider openai-codex --plain` against that config.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```console\n$ proof_dir=$(mktemp -d /tmp/openclaw-94184-proof.XXXXXX)\n$ printf '%s\\n' '{\"plugins\":{\"entries\":{\"codex\":{\"enabled\":true}}}}' > \"$proof_dir/openclaw.json\"\n$ OPENCLAW_HOME=\"$proof_dir/home\" OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=\"$proof_dir/state\" OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=\"$proof_dir/openclaw.json\" OPENCLAW_CODEX_DISCOVERY_LIVE=0 pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider openai-codex --plain\n$ node scripts/run-node.mjs models list --all --provider openai-codex --plain\ncodex/gpt-5.4-mini\ncodex/gpt-5.5\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The legacy `--provider openai-codex` filter accepted the alias and returned the Codex catalog rows instead of `No models found`.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Codex OAuth/app-server network discovery; this proof intentionally uses the static Codex catalog fallback.",
